  "notes": "Fixed discover top status overlap by replacing fixed-pixel internal grid with proportional columns and adding overflow/truncation guards. Build passed. Playwright desktop/narrow-desktop overlap checks passed with screenshots. Follow-up fixed recommended echo panel vertical overflow with clamp-scaled spacing/rows; Playwright overflowBottom=0 on desktop and narrow desktop. Follow-up removed nonfunctional list/map discover view controls, kept a grid indicator, and right-aligned the remaining sort controls; Playwright confirmed no list/map controls, rightGap=0, and no horizontal overflow on light desktop/narrow desktop. Follow-up removed nonfunctional world-time chevron and changed the world-time card from button to non-interactive div; Playwright confirmed DIV tag, one remaining SVG, default cursor, and no horizontal overflow on light desktop/narrow desktop. Follow-up corrected sidebar logo/nav geometry: logo centered, nav x/w balanced, labels nowrap+truncate; Playwright confirmed balanced active/logo gaps, no wrapped labels, and no horizontal overflow. Follow-up increased discover main gutter by moving title, filters, result header, and card grid left edge to x=252 while preserving right rail clearance; Playwright measured left gutter 28.47px at 1366, 21.34px at 1024, 17.88px at 858, no horizontal overflow. Follow-up fixed discover card entry before data load: route now passes loading state, fallback cards render disabled without href while loading, header shows 加载中, and loaded cards link to /tavern/{id}; Playwright confirmed initial DIV/no href then loaded A href and successful navigation. Follow-up fixed right-rail entry and favorite behavior: loading rows now disabled with no links, loaded rows link to /tavern/{id}, and recommended/footprint heart buttons toggle persistent red filled favorite state without navigating; Playwright confirmed loading/no-link, loaded /tavern links, favorite aria-pressed true/red hearts, and row navigation. Follow-up fixed homepage recommended coordinate card entry before data load: route now passes loading state, fallback cards render disabled without href while loading on desktop/mobile, and loaded cards link to /tavern/{id}; Playwright confirmed desktop and narrow initial DIV/no href then loaded A href and click navigation in under 600ms. Follow-up restricted light theme to designed pages only: root light class now applies only on / and /discover, ProductShell pages force dark even when saved preference is light, and ProductShell no longer shows a theme toggle; Playwright confirmed /discover remains light while /tavern/pw_lantern_helpdesk is dark on desktop and narrow with no horizontal overflow. Follow-up removed the tavern chat assist sidecar from the chat workbench; scene recap/starter prompt/social-memory debug sidecar code was deleted, leaving only folded space functions and mini-games below chat. Playwright confirmed chat assist/current scene/starter text absent on desktop and narrow, dark theme, and no horizontal overflow. Follow-up moved engagement summary out of tavern page and into visitor personal center: tavern public panel no longer renders the per-space coin/gift card, /home-me now shows a visitor-level aggregate asset summary, and a route alias file keeps existing /home-me links working. Initial build failed due duplicate route id when alias pointed at the same module; fixed by home-me-alias.tsx and final build passed. Playwright confirmed tavern coin panel absent and visitor summary visible with no horizontal overflow. Follow-up further trimmed tavern secondary tools to invite and private feedback only: route public panel now renders only share and feedback cards, the folded section is titled 邀请与反馈, and the mini-game secondary section was removed. Playwright confirmed invite/feedback present, creator-conversion/neighborhood rumor/mini-game/special type/coin panels absent, one detail section, and no horizontal overflow. Follow-up audited visible visitor-facing copy across tavern, personal center, create, guide, notifications, dedicated management, and related panels; rewrote implementation/developer wording into user-facing actions while preserving routing/API identifiers; build passed and Playwright copy audit passed on desktop+narrow with failures/pageErrors empty. Follow-up removed tavern doorway/first-minute guide panels because they duplicated chat entry and consumed first-screen space; build passed and Playwright confirmed doorway/first-minute DOM absent, chat grid/invite-feedback present, no overflow on desktop+narrow. Follow-up removed visitor composer rule/identity controls: conversation intent chips and speaker identity settings are gone, send path no longer injects intent context, build passed, and Playwright confirmed direct composer only on desktop+narrow. Follow-up simplified the tavern entrance/welcome copy: removed public-channel/@NPC/task/plot onboarding text from the generated shopkeeper message and softened adjacent public-chat hints/placeholders; legacy product chat room was kept in parity. Build passed and Playwright confirmed exact welcome text, no banned onboarding terms, natural placeholder, and no horizontal overflow on desktop+narrow. Follow-up removed rule-like intro from the tavern chat area: the large public-channel explanation card is now a compact title row, Why Here/first-minute style panels remain absent, keyboard/@NPC/task guidance is no longer visible, and legacy input hints were softened. Build passed and Playwright confirmed desktop+narrow stageText=公共聊天, no banned rule/onboarding terms, no Why Here panel, and no horizontal overflow. Follow-up stripped the tavern visitor chat shell down to direct chat: removed the hero description, status/coordinate/LLM chips, channel teaching copy, duplicate NPC seat gallery, NPC description blurbs, and folded tool description. Build passed and Playwright checked both 8950 backend-served and 5173 dev-served routes on desktop+narrow: welcome visible, no doorway/first-minute/guide/rule terms, no stale metadata chips, no horizontal overflow. Follow-up changed NPC list clicks from public @ targeting to private rooms: selecting an NPC now switches data-active-chat-channel to private, clears composer text, creates a one-on-one greeting reaction if the private room has no messages, and no longer shows/sets target banners or @ mentions. Legacy chat room received the same private entrance seeding. Build passed and Playwright checked 8950+5173 desktop/narrow: clicking 桥桥 enters private, stageText=桥桥, private greeting visible, no @ insertion, no public shopkeeper leak, no overflow.",
